{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/waitUntil(mutex:endTime:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"method","title":"waitUntil(mutex:endTime:)","extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"waitUntil"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"mutex","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"endTime"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gint64","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gint64","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib12CondProtocolPAAE9waitUntil5mutex7endTimeSbqd___s5Int64VtAA05MutexC0Rd__lF"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"waitUntil"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"mutex","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"endTime"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gint64","text":"gint64","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" it is possible that a spurious or stolen wakeup","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"could occur.  For that reason, waiting on a condition variable should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always be in a loop, based on an explicitly-checked predicate."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" is returned if the condition variable was signalled (or in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"case of a spurious wakeup).  ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is returned if ","type":"text"},{"code":"endTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following code shows how to correctly perform a timed wait on a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition variable (extending the example presented in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"documentation for "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["gpointer","pop_data_timed (void)","{","  gint64 end_time;","  gpointer data;","","  g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","","  end_time = g_get_monotonic_time () + 5 * G_TIME_SPAN_SECOND;","  while (!current_data)","    if (!g_cond_wait_until (&data_cond, &data_mutex, end_time))","      {","        \/\/ timeout has passed.","        g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","        return NULL;","      }","","  \/\/ there is data for us","  data = current_data;","  current_data = NULL;","","  g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","  return data;","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice that the end time is calculated once, before entering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"loop and reused.  This is the motivation behind the use of absolute","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"time on this API – if a relative time of 5 seconds were passed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly to the call and a spurious wakeup occurred, the program would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have to start over waiting again (which would lead to a total wait","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"time of more than 5 seconds).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Waits until either "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cond"},{"text":" is signalled or ","type":"text"},{"code":"endTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has passed."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol\/waituntil(mutex:endtime:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondProtocol":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CondProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"CondProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CondProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition. Threads can block on a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" if they find a certain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition they signal the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", and that causes the waiting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads to be woken up."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"access.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Mutex","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondProtocol/waitUntil(mutex:endTime:)":{"type":"topic","title":"waitUntil(mutex:endTime:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol\/waituntil(mutex:endtime:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"waitUntil","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"mutex","kind":"externalPara